<component id="ID_txt04">
<text><![CDATA[<ul><li>Private addresses are used and routed internally but are not routed on the Internet.</li><br/><li>NAT translates private addresses into public addresses that route into the Internet.</li><br/><li>Static NAT maps a single inside local address to a single inside global (public) address.</li><br/><li>Dynamic NAT uses an available pool of public addresses and assigns them to inside local addresses.</li><br/><li>PAT translates multiple local addresses to a single global IP address.</li></ul>]]></text>
</component>


